# ESSENSYS UX Matrix Gate

Any UI-facing ESSENSYS feature must prove non-regression on at least:

- desktop / ordinateur
- iPhone
- iPad

This is a merge gate, not a best-effort note.

## Required manifest contract

For UI features, `features/<id>.json` must include:

```json
"tests": {
  "playwright": ["e2e/tests/<feature>.spec.ts"],
  "coverage_must_test": ["..."],
  "ux_matrix": {
    "required": true,
    "devices": ["desktop", "iphone", "ipad"],
    "required_projects": ["support-desktop", "support-iphone", "support-ipad"],
    "screenshots_required": true,
    "visual_regression_required": true,
    "no_armoire_required": true
  },
  "ux_evidence": {
    "devices_validated": ["desktop", "iphone", "ipad"],
    "status": "passed"
  }
}
```

Use `no_armoire_required=true` for domotic UIs that could send actions to firmware, gateway, cloud relay, scenarios, shutters, lights or `/inject` endpoints.

## Required Playwright annotations

Every UX matrix spec should include visible annotations near the suite header:

```ts
// @feature: <feature-id>
// @spec: openspec/changes/<change>/specs/<capability>/spec.md
// @devices: desktop,iphone,ipad
// @no-armoire
```

Project names must also make device coverage obvious, e.g. `support-desktop`, `support-iphone`, `support-ipad`.

## Required checks

Run before done:

```bash
python3 scripts/feature_lifecycle/validate_feature_manifests.py
python3 scripts/feature_lifecycle/check_feature_gate.py --strict
```

In frontend repos, also run the UX matrix command exposed by the repo, for example:

```bash
npm run test:matrix -- --project=support-desktop --project=support-iphone --project=support-ipad
```

## No-armoire safety

Tests must block real mutations unless dry-run is explicit. Block or mock:

- `/api/admin/inject`
- `/api/portal/inject`
- `/api/web/actions`
- `/scenarios/*/launch`
- any POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE that could reach a real armoire

## Done criteria

- Feature manifest has `tests.ux_matrix`.
- Desktop, iPhone and iPad are declared and evidenced.
- Playwright report/screenshots are uploaded or linked when available.
- `check_feature_gate.py --strict` passes.
- No real armoire action can be emitted during tests.
